{{!
    @template local_wunderbyte_table/filter_treenode

    One (sub)tree level of a treefilter (see the treefilter class). Renders the list for the current
    level: one selectable checkbox per node and, for nodes with children, a nested list rendered by
    recursively including this same partial — giving an arbitrarily deep tree. Selecting a node
    filters to that node's whole subtree (expanded server-side). The partial is rooted at the <ul>
    (not the <li>) so each rendered fragment is complete, valid flow content.

    Context variables required for this template:
    * istoplist - bool, true only on the outermost context: styles the list as the filter panel root.
      Shadowed with false on every node so it cannot leak down the mustache context stack.
    * children - array of nodes to render on this level, each carrying:
      * key - the node label
      * value - the node id (submitted as the filter value)
      * count - number of records in the node's subtree
      * identifier - unique-per-render id fragment
      * category - the filter column name (checkbox field name)
      * haschildren - bool, whether children is non-empty
      * children - array of child nodes (same shape)
    * columnname, idstring - resolved from the enclosing filter context

    Example context (json):
    {
        "istoplist": true,
        "children": [
            {
                "key": "Building A",
                "value": 12,
                "count": 5,
                "identifier": "id12",
                "category": "entityid",
                "haschildren": true,
                "istoplist": false,
                "children": [
                    { "key": "Floor 1", "value": 13, "count": 5, "identifier": "id13", "category": "entityid", "haschildren": false, "istoplist": false, "children": [] }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}}
<ul class="wunderbyterFilterList {{#istoplist}}treehierarchy pt-2 list-group-flush{{/istoplist}}{{^istoplist}}wbt-treechildren{{/istoplist}}"{{#istoplist}} data-moodletype="treelist"{{/istoplist}}>
    {{#children}}
        <li class="form-check wbt-treenode">
            <input class="filterelement form-check-input wbt-treenode-checkbox" type="checkbox" value="{{value}}" id="{{identifier}}{{columnname}}{{idstring}}" {{checked}} name="{{category}}" data-action="csshide" data-key="{{key}}" data-targetvalue="{{value}}">
            <label class="form-check-label" for="{{identifier}}{{columnname}}{{idstring}}">
                <span class="filterkeylabel">{{key}}</span> <span class="filtercountlabel">{{#count}}({{count}}){{/count}}</span>
            </label>
            {{#haschildren}}
                {{> local_wunderbyte_table/filter_treenode }}
            {{/haschildren}}
        </li>
    {{/children}}
</ul>
